found, and it's not just

00:40:57.040 --> 00:40:59.510
with "Itchy Feet," it's
with writing as well,

00:40:59.510 --> 00:41:02.430
that a big part of
the creative process

00:41:02.430 --> 00:41:04.967
is staring blankly into
space or staring at a wall

00:41:04.967 --> 00:41:06.050
and accomplishing nothing.

00:41:06.050 --> 00:41:08.008
Or you think you're not
accomplishing anything.

00:41:08.008 --> 00:41:10.680
In reality, what you're doing
is you're working on it,

00:41:10.680 --> 00:41:12.977
you're stewing it,
you're cooking it.

00:41:12.977 --> 00:41:14.560
But it feels like a
lot of wasted time

00:41:14.560 --> 00:41:17.970
that you're sitting
starting at a wall.

00:41:17.970 --> 00:41:22.800
And I used to hate that part
of it until I read about Pixar.

00:41:22.800 --> 00:41:26.180
That they actually,
they know that this

00:41:26.180 --> 00:41:27.710
is how the creative
process works

00:41:27.710 --> 00:41:30.220
and they schedule that
time into their development

00:41:30.220 --> 00:41:34.060
of their stories so that
when they hit the wall,

00:41:34.060 --> 00:41:36.265
even if it's a big group
of genius storytellers,

00:41:36.265 --> 00:41:38.640
they hit the wall, they can't
figure out what to do next,

00:41:38.640 --> 00:41:39.830
and they go like,
all right, well,

00:41:39.830 --> 00:41:41.710
let's go do something
else for a couple days.

00:41:41.710 --> 00:41:43.500
And it's planned.

00:41:43.500 --> 00:41:45.477
They plan this block.

00:41:45.477 --> 00:41:47.060
This section where
you're just sitting

00:41:47.060 --> 00:41:49.018
there banging your head
against an idea and you

00:41:49.018 --> 00:41:51.100
can't think of something.

00:41:51.100 --> 00:41:55.530
So to answer your question,
usually like a couple hours.

00:41:55.530 --> 00:41:58.280
Usually, I sit there and
I'll have blocked this time

00:41:58.280 --> 00:41:59.270
aside to do it.

00:41:59.270 --> 00:42:01.930
So I'll sit there and
go, OK, this is the idea.

00:42:01.930 --> 00:42:02.780
That doesn't work.

00:42:02.780 --> 00:42:03.350
That doesn't work.

00:42:03.350 --> 00:42:04.183
Oh, this would work.

00:42:04.183 --> 00:42:05.370
Nah, that doesn't work.

00:42:05.370 --> 00:42:07.060
And then a couple
hours later, like

00:42:07.060 --> 00:42:10.730
once it clicks, and I, like I
said, I get the sketch down,

00:42:10.730 --> 00:42:14.217
